node.text: Skateboarders giving back to skateboarding! Salad days is a non-profit that @nestorjudkins created as a way to give back to skateboarding. He takes used decks trucks wheels and whatever else he can  to underdeveloped communities all over the world to spread the power and love of skateboarding. Here’s a behind the scenes road tripping across Southern India with @holystoked.  Click the link to see the whole story in episode one of the new “Postcard” series we are doing as a collaboration between @enjoi and @saladdaysofskateboarding now playing on our YouTube channel.  Click link in bio

node.text:
This is the first episode in a new series in collaboration with @enjoi and @saladdaysofskateboarding.
Link in bio.
In January, 2019, my friend Zack and I flew to bangalore, India to join @holystoked on their annual road trip across southern India to hit up a bunch of DIY skateparks they have built over the years. We didn’t really know what to expect but just wanted to check out the scene this crew of skaters are building in India. Since then, I was inspire to form a nonprofit @saladdaysofskateboaring and we put together this glimpse into what I think is an epic story of skateboarding’s ability to transcend all borders and cultures. More “Postcard” episodes to come in the near future. Don’t forget to write.
❤️
Nestor

📽&🎬 by @hollazack

node.text:
Today, Thursday 14th May 2020 marks one year since Ben Raemers tragically took his own life. It’s an emotional day today to say the least. when I’m missing him the most, I tend to go searching on YouTube for him... no I don’t get to interact with him, but thru those videos  I do get to feel that energy and beauty that was Ben. watching Ben parts always puts a smile on my face. and although he is gone, those videos, thankfully will be there for us forever..
I wanted to share with you all his part from oververt. From how stoked he was out with the boys filming for it to the wacky outfits he was wearing during that period, I know watching it always puts a smile on my face. 
Bens family and @thebenraemersfoundation have started the hashtag #SMiLeForRaemers so shoot a photo of yourself smiling for ben today and make sure to tag @thebenraemersfoundation, and they are gonna share all the SMiLes  today. ❤️ .
#thebenraemersfoundation

node.text: Cairo is a beast. During filming for oververt cairo was also doing TM duties for the brand. Driving the van, getting the bro’s waters, stroking egos, ect. And all the while still going harder than anyone else on the board!! The nollie flip session down the double set really sums up cairo. We drove around all day going from spot to spot that the dudes would just look at and not skate. Rolled up to this double set for one of the guys to skate, they didn’t want to, so cairo stepped up and just started jumping! He went to war on that thing and didn’t give up and got the trick. One day I got a call from him that he didn’t feel comfortable having a board on the wall next to all the young ripping pros out there.. I told him cairo, you deserve it. You can “milk it” for as long as you want. You we earned that. Putting in work from real to popwar to that lakai part, you bled for it and you earned your place to say I’m just gonna cruise and milk it a bit.. but he didn’t want that! Cairo isn’t ever gonna take it for free or take the easy way. His skating shows that! Even now that he is retired with a desk job he is still crushing harder than a lot of pros out there!! Love you cairo! You are forever one of the greats to ever do it!

node.text:
@zackwallin -
Ahh 2013....the main year filming for oververt.  Wouldn’t take that year back for anything. Just recovered from a blood clot in my chest & could not be more hyped to be out filming for a full length video for Enjoi.
Just being a hungry AM involved with some Enjoi big hitters like Wieger, Cairo & Louie was tons of motivation. Plus having the combination of traveling the world with good filmers/photographers topped everything off.
I remember going back for the kick flip over the street gap a total of seven times. Once I actually landed It I remember being so damn hyped that I was able to push my self that far the feeling stuck with me for days.
I had that happen muiltiple times filming for oververt & it was rad seeing it happen with other people filming for the video!🤙🏼

node.text:
I think @wiegervw part is my favorite part ive ever edited, I think its because of how hyped he was when we showed him the part. I love the fact that we start it off with me slamming into him. it was fun editing because of weigers  sense of humor we could do things like the "obligatory" rill up shot and the speak and spell intro with Jose not being able to spell his name. I had to actually download speak and spell sounds and manipulated a few words to be able to get it to sound like it properly pronounces weiger. when we started filming for oververt  I really wanted weiger who was known for heel flip tricks to get a proper kick flip in his part. at the time I was really hyped to get a kick flip out of him at the end of the line. you can actually hear me say "do a kick flip" but for me the icing on the cake was his ender ended up being the inward heel to front tail kick flip out on a ledge in Lyon. it quite possibly was the best kick flip he's ever done. 
love you weiggy - @the_breadcrumb_trail
